<img src="/web/20121026064554im_/http://mlb.mlb.com/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10"/><br/>


<table width="581" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
	<tr valign="top">
		<td width="375">
<b>THE ASTRODOME, HOUSTON, TEXAS</b> -- After splitting the first two games of the 1980 NLCS, the Philadelphia Phillies and Houston Astros headed to the Astrodome to see who could gain the upper hand in the all-important swing game in a five-game series, Game 3.  The Astros, who relied heavily on team speed and strong pitching to win ballgames, sent veteran knuckleballer <b>Joe Niekro</b> to the mound to defend their home (astro) turf.  The Phillies countered with <b>Larry Christenson</b>, a former 19-game winner, to hold off the 'Stros and allow the big bats of <b>Mike Schmidt</b>, <b>Greg Luzinski</b> and <b>Pete Rose</b> to do the damage.<p/>


